Name: adult central nervous system mature teratoma
Definition: A leukemia that arises from changes in the tissues forming white blood cells and characterized by a normal or decreased number of white blood cells in the circulating blood.
Synonym: teratoma of the adult central nervous system

Name: childhood central nervous system mature teratoma
Definition: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells and derives_from epithelial cells.
Synonym: Ventricular septal defect with pulmonary stenosis or atresia

Name: obsolete pediatric CNS teratoma
Definition: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells and derives_from epithelial cells.
Synonym: pediatric teratoma of central nervous system
